Copernicus (lunar crater).label: Copernicus
Copernicus (lunar crater).description: Copernicus is a lunar impact crater named after the astronomer Nicolaus Copernicus, located in eastern Oceanus Procellarum .It typifies craters that formed during the Copernican period in that it has a prominent ray system. Wikipedia

Langrenus (crater).label: Langrenus
Langrenus (crater).description: Langrenus is a prominent impact crater located near the eastern lunar limb. The feature is circular in shape, but appears oblong due to foreshortening. It lies on the eastern shore of the Mare Fecunditatis. Wikipedia

Ptolemaeus (lunar crater).label: Ptolemaeus
Ptolemaeus (lunar crater).description: Ptolemaeus is an ancient lunar impact crater close to the center of the near side, named for Claudius Ptolemy, the Greco-Roman writer, mathematician, astronomer, geographer and astrologer. Wikipedia

Tycho (crater).label: Tycho
Tycho (crater).description: Tycho is a prominent lunar impact crater located in the southern lunar highlands, named after the Danish astronomer Tycho Brahe. To the south is the crater Street; to the east is Pictet, and to the north-northeast is Sasserides. Wikipedia

Blancanus (crater).label: Blancanus
Blancanus (crater).description: Blancanus is a lunar impact crater located in the rugged southern region of the Moon, to the southwest of the walled plain Clavius. To the northwest lies the comparably sized crater Scheiner, and south-southwest of Blancanus is the worn Klaproth. Wikipedia

Campanus (crater).label: Campanus
Campanus (crater).description: Campanus is a lunar impact crater that is located on the southwestern edge of Mare Nubium. It forms a crater pair with Mercator just to the southeast. Along the southern rampart of Campanus is the small lunar mare named Palus Epidemiarum. Wikipedia

Ariadaeus (crater).label: Ariadaeus
Ariadaeus (crater).description: Ariadaeus is a small, bowl-shaped lunar impact crater on the western shores of Mare Tranquillitatis. It lies to the north of the crater Dionysius, and to the west-southwest of Arago. Wikipedia

Aristarchus (crater).label: Aristarchus
Aristarchus (crater).description: Aristarchus, named after the Greek astronomer Aristarchus of Samos, is a prominent lunar impact crater that lies in the northwest part of the Moon's near side. Wikipedia

Capuanus (crater).label: Capuanus
Capuanus (crater).description: Capuanus is a lunar crater that lies along the southern edge of the Palus Epidemiarum. The outer rim is eroded and indented by lesser crater impacts, with notches in the north, west, and southern parts of the rim. Wikipedia
